Glencore Decides Against New Copper Mine in Serbia, Novosti Says

-- B y   M i s h a   S a v i c
-- 
2011-03-24T09:11:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-24/glencore-decides-against-new-copper-mine-in-serbia-novosti-says.html
Switzerland ’s Glencore
International AG will not open a copper mine in eastern  Serbia 
after testing showed lower than expected copper content,
 Vecernje Novosti  newspaper reported, citing local authorities it
did not identify.  Glencore, the world’s largest commodity trader, had eyed
the Cerovo location, close to Serbia’s existing copper mine and
smelter, state-run  RTB Bor , with which it had considered a
partnership for opening a new mine, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Misha Savic in Belgrade at 
 msavic2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  